I don't think we need the `if` check at the beginning? if self._raw_amqp_message.annotations is None, then `self._raw_amqp_message.annotations.get` triggers `AttributeError`, and we just return `ServiceBusMessageState.ACTIVE` in the except case

```suggestion
        try:
            message_state = self._raw_amqp_message.annotations.get(MESSAGE_STATE_NAME)
            return (
                ServiceBusMessageState.DEFERRED if message_state == 1
                else ServiceBusMessageState.SCHEDULED if message_state == 2
                else ServiceBusMessageState.ACTIVE
            )
        except AttributeError:
            return ServiceBusMessageState.ACTIVE
```

@abtink If KeyRefs are not used we `otPlatCryptoDestroyKey` would not be implemented and would be an empty function in crypto_platform.cpp, so it will be an empty call.

We need to destroy these keys here because after generating the keys, key_manager will not store these references, so when new keys are created, it does not have the old keys to destroy them, unless we instantiate Mac in key_manager, which I wanted to avoid.

Yes, I thought of using it as a list and destroying only the previous key, but this will not work if the NetworkKey itself is changed, There is not way for Mac to know if the update is because of networkkey update or keySeqnumber update. It is better to assume that these are new keys and treat them this way.

