I prefer to sticking to regular dispatcher "layout" here:

1. It took me a few glances to actually see that we indeed have a `return inpt.to(dtype)` there. I think this comes from the fact that all other dispatchers don't do this. This is likely only going to happen to us maintainers since the code is clear, but still.
2. Right now, the dispatcher supports all tensors. Although I agree that `to_dtype` is general enough to allow this, all other dispatchers only support plain tensors and datapoints. And since for all other cases this is just a fancy wrapper around `t.to(dtype)`, I don't see a point of supporting that here.

