@dorodnic, I don't think you meant the case of functions that don't have a way to check to success or failure besides checking `e`
```C++
rs2_error e;
rs2_set_option(options, option, 0, &e); // no return value to check for success
if (e)
   rs2_free_error(e);
```
since this would crash currently and likewise for ignoring the return value
```c++
rs2_error *e; // random garbage
rs2_get_frame_width(frame, &e);
if (e) rs2_free_error(e);
```
because this would currently crash on success as well.  This case would also currently crash on success,
```c++
rs2_error *e;
if (!rs2_get_frame_width(frame,&e) || e)
   rs2_free_error(e);
```
so maybe you meant meant functions that you can check for failure without checking `e` like this
```
rs2_error *e;
if (!rs2_get_frame_height(frame,&e) && e)
   rs2_free_error(e);
```
which would currently work in both the success and failure cases, but crash in the success case with both of my suggestions because `e` is uninitialized.   The good thing here is this has a chance of being noticed quickly.

FWIW, my searching this repo shows no uninitialized uses of `rs2_error`.

If you are otherwise happy with the changes here, I'd be happy to move these two to their own PR, drop them completely, or you can just merge the commit before them by hand and we can continue the discussion here.

